7. aeluros. Most of the MSS. have ‘caeruleos:‘ which has been interpreted as ‘salt-water fish’ as contrasted with ‘piscem fluminis;’ the Pithoean has ‘aeruleos’ The reading in the text is that generally adopted. Egypt was the home of the cat, which was actually used for the purposes of the chase. The Greeks and Romans domesticated some kind of weasel, and applied the name of αἴλουρος to the Egyptian cat. See Hehn p. 376. On Egyptian cat worship see Sharpe‚ History of Egypt vol. ii. p. 23- Diodorus Siculus, i. 84. ᾗ 1, describes how the Egyptian populace killed a Roman soldier who had killed a cat unawares.
